## 🏗️ 9 Steps to Nx Integration (Real Syntax)

### 1. Prepare the Workspace
Restructure your repo so apps and libs are clearly separated:
```bash
mkdir apps libs
mv admin-api apps/
mv admin-ui apps/
mv user-api apps/
mv user-ui apps/
mkdir -p libs/shared libs/ui
```

---

### 2. Initialize Nx
At the root:
```bash
npx nx init
```

---

### 3. Generate App Configs
Scaffold `project.json` for each app:
```bash
npx nx generate @nrwl/node:application admin-api --directory=apps
npx nx generate @nrwl/web:application admin-ui --directory=apps
npx nx generate @nrwl/node:application user-api --directory=apps
npx nx generate @nrwl/web:application user-ui --directory=apps
```

---

### 4. Generate Library Configs
```bash
npx nx generate @nrwl/js:library shared --directory=libs
npx nx generate @nrwl/js:library ui --directory=libs
```

---

### 5. Add Custom Docker Targets
Inject `docker-build` and `docker-push`:
```bash
npx nx generate @nrwl/workspace:run-commands \
  --project=admin-api \
  --name=docker-build \
  --command="docker build -t {args.imageName}:{args.tag} apps/admin-api" \
  --inputs=imageName,tag

npx nx generate @nrwl/workspace:run-commands \
  --project=admin-api \
  --name=docker-push \
  --command="docker push {args.imageName}:{args.tag}" \
  --inputs=imageName,tag
```
Repeat for `admin-ui`, `user-api`, `user-ui`.

---

### 6. Configure `nx.json`
Add cacheable operations:
```json
{
  "tasksRunnerOptions": {
    "default": {
      "options": {
        "cacheableOperations": [
          "build",
          "lint",
          "test",
          "docker-build",
          "docker-push"
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

### 7. Verify Dependency Graph
```bash
npx nx graph
```
Open the graph in your browser to confirm apps depend on `libs/shared` and `libs/ui`.

---

### 8. CI Pipeline (`.github/workflows/ci.yaml`)
```yaml
name: CI Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ main ]
  workflow_dispatch:

jobs:
  ci:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 20
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npx nx affected --target=lint --parallel=3
      - run: npx nx affected --target=test --parallel=3
      - run: npx nx affected --target=build --parallel=3
      - run: npx nx affected --target=docker-build --args="--imageName=my-org/{projectName} --tag=${GITHUB_SHA}"
      - run: npx nx affected --target=docker-push --args="--imageName=my-org/{projectName} --tag=${GITHUB_SHA}"
```

---

### 9. CD Pipeline (`.github/workflows/deploy.yaml`)
```yaml
name: CD Pipeline

on:
  workflow_run:
    workflows: ["CI Pipeline"]
    types: [completed]
  workflow_dispatch:

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.event.workflow_run.conclusion == 'success'
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: azure/setup-kubectl@v3
        with:
          version: 'latest'
      - run: echo "${{ secrets.KUBECONFIG_DATA }}" > $HOME/.kube/config
      - run: npx nx affected --target=deploy --args="--tag=${GITHUB_SHA}"
```

And in each app’s `project.json`:
```json
"deploy": {
  "executor": "nx:run-commands",
  "options": {
    "command": "kubectl set image deployment/admin-api admin-api=my-org/admin-api:{args.tag} --record"
  },
  "inputs": ["tag"]
}
```

